foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: In its administrative appeal backlog projections issued November 1, 2007, OIP initially identified its number of appeals pending as of the start of the fiscal year as 1,580. A subsequent audit of its appeal database led to the adjustment of this pending appeal number to 1,530.

foia:AppealDispositionSection.foia:FootnoteText: OIP's appeal database makes no distinction between partial and complete affirmance or reversal/remand of a request, so this number necessarily includes some appeals that were affirmed or reversed/remanded in part. For the last quarter of fiscal year 2008, OIP hand-tabulated the closed appeals to differentiate between the partially and completely affirmed or reversed/remanded appeals. The chart below contains this data. It is a subset of the data above, reflecting the last quarter of the fiscal year.

foia:ProcessedResponseTimeSection.foia:FootnoteText: When a component responded to fewer than three requests, no median or average number of days pending has been calculated.
Certain components' systems count calendar days rather than working days.
Certain components' systems could not separate perfected and non-perfected requests. EOIR's and JMD's systems were unable to separate perfected from non-perfected for their pending requests.

USPC is unable to provide data that distinguishes between "simple" and "complex" requests. For reporting purposes, all requests are reported in the complex track. USPC did not receive any requests for expedited processing in Fiscal Year 2008

foia:InformationGrantedResponseTimeSecti.foia:FootnoteText: When a component responded to fewer than three requests no median or average number of days pending has been calculated.

foia:ComplexResponseTimeIncrementsSectio.foia:FootnoteText: The Criminal Division closed a total of 549 FOIA requests that were in the "401+ days" category, which is approximately thirty-nine percent of the total that were closed in Fiscal Year 2008.

foia:PendingPerfectedRequestsSection.foia:FootnoteText: When a component had fewer than three pending perfected requests the average number of days was also used as the median.

foia:ExpeditedProcessingSection.foia:FootnoteText: When a component responded to fewer than three requests for expedited processing the average number of days was also used as the median.

foia:FeeWaiverSection.foia:FootnoteText: When a component responded to fewer than three requests for a fee waiver the average number of days was also used as the median.

For this Section OIP is reporting requests for fee waivers first made at the appeals level during the fourth quarter of Fiscal Year 2008.
